SYSTEMCTL : 

    START A SERVICE : sudo systemctl start ServiceName

    CHECK STATUS OF SERVICE : sudo systemctl status ServiceName

    STOP A SERVICE : sudo systemctl stop ServiceName

    RESTART A SERVICE : sudo systemctl restart ServiceName

    START SERVICE WHEN SYSTEM REBOOT : sudo systemctl enable --now ServiceName

    DISABLE SERVICE : sudo systemctl disable ServiceName
            
    CHECK SERVICE ENABLED OR NOT : sudo systemctl is-enabled --now ServiceName

    PREVENT SERVICE START : sudo systemctl mask ServiceName

    REMOVE MASK FROM SERVICE : sudo systemctl unmask ServiceName

    LIST RUNNING SERVICES : sudo systemctl | grep -i running

